I have the complete type definitions. Here is a comprehensive answer to all your questions.

---

## Library: @clack/prompts (v1.0.1)

### 1. Does it have a progress bar?

**Yes.** There is a `progress()` function (lines 295-303 in the type definitions). It extends the spinner with progress-bar capabilities:

```typescript
interface ProgressOptions extends SpinnerOptions {
    style?: 'light' | 'heavy' | 'block';
    max?: number;
    size?: number;
}

interface ProgressResult extends SpinnerResult {
    advance(step?: number, msg?: string): void;
}

declare function progress(opts?: ProgressOptions): ProgressResult;
```

It inherits all spinner methods (`start`, `stop`, `cancel`, `error`, `message`, `clear`) and adds `advance(step?, msg?)` to increment the progress bar. Three visual styles are available: `'light'`, `'heavy'`, and `'block'`.

### 2. Does it have a task list / task runner display?

**Yes.** There are **two** task-related primitives:

#### `tasks()` -- Sequential task runner with status indicators

```typescript
type Task = {
    title: string;
    task: (message: (string: string) => void) => string | Promise<string> | void | Promise<void>;
    enabled?: boolean;
};

declare const tasks: (tasks: Task[], opts?: CommonOptions) => Promise<void>;
```

This runs an array of tasks sequentially, showing a spinner for each one. Each task gets a `message` callback to update its status text while running. Tasks can be conditionally skipped with `enabled: false`. When a task completes, it shows a checkmark with the task title (or the returned string as the completion message).

#### `taskLog()` -- Streaming log display for a single long-running task

```typescript
interface TaskLogOptions extends CommonOptions {
    title: string;
    limit?: number;
    spacing?: number;
    retainLog?: boolean;
}

declare const taskLog: (opts: TaskLogOptions) => {
    message(msg: string, mopts?: TaskLogMessageOptions): void;
    group(name: string): {
        message(msg: string, mopts?: TaskLogMessageOptions): void;
        error(message: string): void;
        success(message: string): void;
    };
    error(message: string, opts?: TaskLogCompletionOptions): void;
    success(message: string, opts?: TaskLogCompletionOptions): void;
};
```

This renders a rolling log under a title. You can stream messages into it, organize them into named groups, and finalize with `success()` or `error()`. The `limit` option caps how many log lines are visible. The `retainLog` option controls whether the log output is kept on screen after completion. The `showLog` option on completion controls whether the accumulated log is shown on error/success.

### 3. ALL available components/functions

Here is the complete exported API of `@clack/prompts` v1.0.1:

#### Interactive Prompts (await user input)

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `text(opts)` | Single-line text input with optional placeholder, default value, and validation |
| `password(opts)` | Masked text input (password entry) with configurable mask character |
| `confirm(opts)` | Yes/No confirmation prompt, supports vertical layout |
| `select(opts)` | Single-selection list with scrollable items |
| `multiselect(opts)` | Multi-selection list with checkboxes |
| `groupMultiselect(opts)` | Multi-select organized into named groups, with optional group-level selection |
| `selectKey(opts)` | Select by pressing a key (value must be a string, matched as keypress) |
| `autocomplete(opts)` | Type-ahead single-select with filterable options |
| `autocompleteMultiselect(opts)` | Type-ahead multi-select combining filtering with checkboxes |
| `path(opts)` | File/directory path input with filesystem awareness |
| `group(prompts, opts)` | Chain multiple prompts sequentially, collecting results into an object; supports `onCancel` |

#### Output / Display (no user input)

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `intro(title)` | Opening banner for a CLI session |
| `outro(message)` | Closing banner for a CLI session |
| `cancel(message)` | Cancellation message (typically used when user presses Ctrl+C) |
| `log.message(msg)` | Generic log message |
| `log.info(msg)` | Info-level log (blue icon) |
| `log.success(msg)` | Success-level log (green checkmark) |
| `log.step(msg)` | Step-level log |
| `log.warn(msg)` | Warning-level log (yellow icon) |
| `log.warning(msg)` | Alias for `log.warn()` |
| `log.error(msg)` | Error-level log (red icon) |
| `note(message, title)` | Boxed note/callout with optional title and custom formatting |
| `box(message, title, opts)` | Bordered box with alignment control (`left`/`center`/`right`), configurable width, padding, and border style |
| `stream.message(iterable)` | Stream output token-by-token from an async iterable |
| `stream.info(iterable)` | Streaming info log |
| `stream.success(iterable)` | Streaming success log |
| `stream.step(iterable)` | Streaming step log |
| `stream.warn(iterable)` | Streaming warning log |
| `stream.warning(iterable)` | Alias for `stream.warn()` |
| `stream.error(iterable)` | Streaming error log |

#### Progress / Task Runners

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `spinner(opts)` | Animated spinner with `start`/`stop`/`cancel`/`error`/`message`/`clear` methods; supports `'dots'` and `'timer'` indicator styles, custom frames |
| `progress(opts)` | Progress bar extending spinner; adds `advance(step?, msg?)` with `'light'`/`'heavy'`/`'block'` styles |
| `tasks(tasks)` | Sequential task runner -- runs an array of `{ title, task, enabled? }` showing checkmarks on completion |
| `taskLog(opts)` | Streaming log display for a long-running operation with grouped sub-messages and success/error finalization |

#### Utilities

| Export | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `isCancel(value)` | Check if a prompt result was cancelled (returned `symbol`) |
| `settings` / `updateSettings` / `ClackSettings` | Global settings object for configuring clack behavior |
| `limitOptions(params)` | Helper for paginating/scrolling option lists |
| `unicode` | Boolean indicating whether the terminal supports Unicode |
| `isCI()` | Detect CI environment |
| `isTTY(output)` | Check if a writable stream is a TTY |
| `unicodeOr(c, fallback)` | Return Unicode char or ASCII fallback based on terminal support |
| `symbol(state)` | Get the appropriate symbol for a prompt state (`active`/`cancel`/`error`/`submit`) |
| `symbolBar(state)` | Get the appropriate bar symbol for a prompt state |
| `S_STEP_ACTIVE`, `S_STEP_CANCEL`, `S_STEP_ERROR`, `S_STEP_SUBMIT`, `S_BAR`, `S_BAR_START`, `S_BAR_END`, etc. | Exported Unicode/ASCII symbol constants for building custom UI |

### 4. Is there a `tasks()` function?

**Yes.** `tasks()` is exactly what you described -- it takes an array of task objects and displays them with status indicators (spinner while running, checkmark on completion). Each task definition looks like:

```typescript
{
    title: "Installing dependencies",
    task: async (message) => {
        message("Resolving packages...");
        await install();
        return "Installed 42 packages";  // optional completion message
    },
    enabled: true  // optional, skip if false
}
```

The `message` callback lets you update the spinner text during execution, and the return value (if a string) replaces the title as the completion message.

